WEBVTT

00:01.835 --> 00:03.336
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON "THE HAVES</i>
<i>AND THE HAVE NOTS"...</i>

00:03.336 --> 00:04.505
THAT GIRL IS NOT CRAZY.

00:04.505 --> 00:06.406
NO, SHE'S NOT CRAZY.
SHE'S MENTALLY ILL.

00:06.406 --> 00:08.609
OH, MY GOD. BLACK SEDAN.

00:08.609 --> 00:10.677
YOU NEED TO BE AS OUTRAGED
AS EVERYONE ELSE.

00:10.677 --> 00:11.678
OF COURSE WE ARE.

00:11.678 --> 00:13.013
JEFFERY, I KILLED THAT GIRL.

00:13.013 --> 00:14.414
PLEASE DON'T TURN ME IN!

00:14.414 --> 00:16.683
GET OUT OF HERE!

00:16.683 --> 00:19.419
YOU'RE A JOKE!
GO TO HELL!

00:19.419 --> 00:20.821
WHAT DO I GOTTA DO
TO GET YOU TO STOP THIS?

00:20.821 --> 00:22.856
DIE.
WHAT IS SHE DOING HERE?

00:22.856 --> 00:25.626
THIS EXPLAINS IT.
SHE KNOWS.

00:25.626 --> 00:26.893
IT'S YOUR BROTHER.
WHAT?

00:26.893 --> 00:29.029
HE WAS HIT BY THE GUY
WHO KILLED THE LITTLE GIRL.

00:29.029 --> 00:30.296
SORRY.

00:34.701 --> 00:37.470
<i>I HAVE TO TELL YOU THAT THIS IS</i>
<i>ONE OF THE SADDEST OCCASIONS</i>

00:37.470 --> 00:40.206
<i>I'VE EVER BEEN TO</i>
<i>AS A REPORTER.</i>

00:40.206 --> 00:42.075
<i>TO SEE THAT LITTLE,</i>
<i>SMALL CASKET</i>

00:42.075 --> 00:44.511
<i>AND KNOW THAT A SMALL CHILD'S</i>
<i>LIFE WAS TAKEN ‐‐</i>

00:44.511 --> 00:46.513
<i>IT PUTS IT ALL</i>
<i>INTO PERSPECTIVE.</i>

00:46.513 --> 00:48.982
[ CROWD SHOUTING ]
<i>AND TO THINK THAT THE KILLER,</i>

00:48.982 --> 00:51.084
<i>THE MURDERER WHO WAS</i>
<i>BEHIND THE WHEEL</i>

00:51.084 --> 00:52.753
<i>WOULDN'T EVEN STOP?</i>

00:52.753 --> 00:54.788
<i>IT'S UNREAL, DIANE.</i>

00:54.788 --> 00:57.490
<i>AND THIS COMMUNITY</i>
<i>IS UP IN ARMS.</i>

00:57.490 --> 00:59.359
<i>AS YOU CAN SEE,</i>
<i>THEY'RE MARCHING.</i>

00:59.359 --> 01:00.734
<i>THEY WANT BLOOD.</i>

01:00.734 --> 01:03.069
WHY'D YOU DO THAT?

01:03.069 --> 01:04.137
ENOUGH OF THAT.

01:04.137 --> 01:06.139
JEFFERY, I NEED TO KNOW
WHAT'S GOING ON.

01:06.139 --> 01:07.373
NO, YOU DON'T.

01:07.373 --> 01:08.575
WHY?

01:08.575 --> 01:09.909
'CAUSE IT'S NOT HELPING
ANYTHING.

01:09.909 --> 01:11.044
IT'S ONLY MAKING US
FEEL WORSE.

01:11.044 --> 01:12.879
"US"?

01:12.879 --> 01:14.881
YES, US.

01:14.881 --> 01:17.918
JEFFERY...

01:17.918 --> 01:19.385
YOU DIDN'T DO ANYTHING.

01:19.385 --> 01:21.855
IT IS US.

01:21.855 --> 01:23.857
YOU'RE MY FRIEND.

01:25.959 --> 01:27.127
[ SIGHS ]

01:27.127 --> 01:28.929
WHY?

01:28.929 --> 01:30.396
WHAT DO YOU MEAN, WHY?

01:30.396 --> 01:32.733
AFTER ALL I'VE DONE
TO YOU?

01:32.733 --> 01:37.237
LOOK, A LOT OF THAT
I DESERVED, OKAY?

01:39.205 --> 01:41.675
SORRY FOR LYING TO YOU
ABOUT LAURA.

01:41.675 --> 01:43.944
[ INHALES AND SIGHS ]

01:43.944 --> 01:45.946
JEFFERY, THAT DOESN'T EVEN
MATTER ANYMORE.

01:45.946 --> 01:47.781
ARE YOU OKAY?

01:47.781 --> 01:49.883
[ SCOFFS ]

01:49.883 --> 01:52.185
[ BREATHES SHARPLY ]

01:52.185 --> 01:54.487
JEFFERY...

01:54.487 --> 01:55.789
I'M SICK TO MY STOMACH.

01:55.789 --> 01:57.223
I KNOW.

01:57.223 --> 01:59.425
SOMEONE IS DEAD.

01:59.425 --> 02:02.769
AND ANOTHER GUY'S
IN THE HOSPITAL.

02:04.004 --> 02:05.539
I KNOW WHO HE IS.

02:05.539 --> 02:08.575
[ Breathes sharply ]
WHAT?

02:08.575 --> 02:10.744
YEAH.

02:13.213 --> 02:16.249
♪♪♪♪♪♪

02:23.990 --> 02:25.325
YOU KNOW HIM?

02:25.325 --> 02:27.928
NO, I‐I DON'T KNOW HIM,
BUT I KNOW WHO HE IS.

02:27.928 --> 02:29.162
WELL, WHO IS HE?

02:29.162 --> 02:31.632
IT'S HANNA'S SON.

02:33.667 --> 02:35.401
HE'S HANNA'S SON?

02:35.401 --> 02:37.103
YES.

02:38.839 --> 02:40.807
OH, MY GOD...

02:40.807 --> 02:42.208
HOW IS HE?

02:43.176 --> 02:44.310
I DON'T KNOW.

02:44.310 --> 02:45.579
JEFFERY, YOU GOTTA FIND OUT.

02:45.579 --> 02:46.613
I'LL TRY.

02:49.482 --> 02:50.884
[ Sighs ] OH...

02:50.884 --> 02:52.786
NO WONDER SHE HASN'T BEEN
HERE AT WORK LATELY.

02:52.786 --> 02:54.888
WYATT, LISTEN TO ME.
YOU CAN'T LET HER KNOW.

02:57.858 --> 02:59.526
JEFFERY, SHE ALREADY KNOWS.

02:59.526 --> 03:01.401
NO, YOU‐YOU CAN'T LET ON
THAT YOU FEEL BAD.

03:01.401 --> 03:02.669
SHE'LL KNOW.

03:02.669 --> 03:04.805
JEFFERY, SHE KNOWS.

03:04.805 --> 03:06.172
WHAT?

03:06.172 --> 03:09.776
WHEN I CAME HOME
THAT NIGHT...

03:09.776 --> 03:11.177
SHE WAS IN THE KITCHEN.

03:11.177 --> 03:13.079
HOW DOES SHE KNOW?

03:13.079 --> 03:14.881
I SAID I HIT SOMEONE.

03:14.881 --> 03:18.118
OH, WYATT.

03:18.118 --> 03:20.486
YEAH, SHE KNOWS.

03:20.486 --> 03:23.890
[ SIGHS ]

03:23.890 --> 03:27.027
[ Groans ] WELL, DID ‐‐
DID YOU SAY WHO YOU HIT?

03:30.396 --> 03:33.734
NO. NO, I SAID, UM...

03:33.734 --> 03:36.670
I‐I JUST CAME IN AND I SAID
I HIT A GUY.

03:36.670 --> 03:38.338
WELL, THEN MAYBE
SHE DOESN'T KNOW.

03:38.338 --> 03:41.141
NO, SHE KNOWS.

03:41.141 --> 03:43.409
SHE CAN SEE RIGHT THROUGH ME
SOMETIMES.

03:43.409 --> 03:45.145
MAN, YOU GOTTA TELL
YOUR DAD.

03:45.145 --> 03:47.180
YEAH, HE WAS THERE, TOO.

03:47.180 --> 03:49.950
HE WAS THERE?
WHAT DID HE SAY?

03:51.417 --> 03:53.820
HE ASKED HER TO LEAVE.

03:53.820 --> 03:56.890
WELL...LET HIM HANDLE IT,
OKAY?

04:00.667 --> 04:02.002
OKAY?

04:02.002 --> 04:04.571
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.

04:04.571 --> 04:10.076
AND ‐‐ BUT YOU HAVE TO ACT
LIKE THIS NEVER HAPPENED.

04:10.076 --> 04:11.344
YOU HAVE TO.

04:12.979 --> 04:14.380
OKAY.

04:14.380 --> 04:16.883
YOU CAN DO IT.
YOU HAVE TO.

04:16.883 --> 04:19.152
[ EXHALES SOFTLY ]

04:19.152 --> 04:20.787
JEFFERY, WHAT HAVE I DONE?

04:20.787 --> 04:23.223
WYATT, THERE'S NOTHING
YOU CAN DO ABOUT IT NOW.

04:23.223 --> 04:24.591
IT'S DONE.

04:24.591 --> 04:27.628
[ BREATHES DEEPLY
AND SIGHS ]

04:27.628 --> 04:29.663
HE'LL FIX THIS.

04:31.698 --> 04:33.867
YOUR DAD WILL FIX THIS.

04:33.867 --> 04:35.368
WILL HE?

04:35.368 --> 04:37.604
YEAH, HE WILL.

04:37.604 --> 04:41.908
JUST DO WHAT HE SAYS,
OKAY?

04:43.176 --> 04:44.511
OKAY.

04:44.511 --> 04:46.780
AND STAY IN THE HOUSE.

04:49.382 --> 04:51.652
OKAY. ALL RIGHT.

04:51.652 --> 04:54.287
ALL RIGHT. I HAVE TO GO.

04:54.287 --> 04:56.823
NO, JEFFERY, STAY WITH ME,
PLEASE. COME ON.

04:56.823 --> 04:58.792
WYATT... [ Sighs ]

04:58.792 --> 05:00.934
WHAT?
I CAN'T.

05:01.902 --> 05:03.236
WHY?

05:03.236 --> 05:05.939
I CAN'T BE AROUND YOU.

05:05.939 --> 05:07.207
WHY?

05:07.207 --> 05:09.175
I‐I JUST ‐‐ I JUST CAN'T.

05:09.175 --> 05:10.877
I GOT ‐‐ I HAVE TO GO.

05:14.347 --> 05:16.683
OKAY.
ALL RIGHT?

05:16.683 --> 05:17.751
JEFFERY, I'M SORRY.

05:17.751 --> 05:20.420
IT'S FINE.

05:20.420 --> 05:22.122
I'M SORRY. HERE.

05:22.122 --> 05:24.357
ALL RIGHT.
ALL RIGHT.

05:24.357 --> 05:25.526
I'M SORRY.
ALL RIGHT.

05:25.526 --> 05:26.827
OKAY.
IT'S OKAY.

05:26.827 --> 05:28.895
YOU'LL BE ALL RIGHT.
WAIT, ARE YOU ‐‐

05:28.895 --> 05:32.365
ARE YOU SURE YOU JUST
CAN'T STAY FOR A LITTLE WHILE?

05:32.365 --> 05:34.434
PLEASE, JEFFERY.

05:38.739 --> 05:41.041
OKAY. I'LL STAY
FOR A LITTLE BIT.

05:41.041 --> 05:42.776
BUT THEN I HAVE TO GO.

05:42.776 --> 05:44.410
OKAY.

05:44.410 --> 05:45.779
THANK YOU.

05:45.779 --> 05:47.113
OKAY.
SIT.

05:47.113 --> 05:48.481
THANKS.

05:48.481 --> 05:51.618
[ <i>WOMAN SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY</i>
<i>OVER P. A.</i> ]

05:51.618 --> 05:54.555
EXCUSE ME. EXCUSE ME.

05:54.555 --> 05:58.124
YOU ‐‐ REALLY?
YOUR FINGER IN MY FACE?

05:58.124 --> 06:00.393
<i>Woman over P. A.:</i>
<i>PAGING DR. BECKER.</i>

06:00.393 --> 06:01.835
<i>PAGING DR. BECKER.</i>

06:01.835 --> 06:04.337
YOU DIDN'T EVEN TELL ME.
YOU DIDN'T EVEN TELL ME!

06:04.337 --> 06:06.239
DON'T YOU JUMP UP IN MY FACE,
LITTLE GIRL.

06:06.239 --> 06:08.274
THAT IS MY BROTHER!
CANDACE, I AM DEALING

06:08.274 --> 06:10.043
WITH WAY TOO MUCH
TO BE DEALING WITH YOU.

06:10.043 --> 06:11.512
YOU SHOULD HAVE TOLD ME.

06:11.512 --> 06:13.246
AND YOU SHOULD HAVE TOLD ME
WHERE YOUR BABY IS.

06:13.246 --> 06:14.881
THAT IS MY CHILD!

06:14.881 --> 06:16.817
AND THAT'S MY CHILD
IN THERE!

06:16.817 --> 06:19.052
AND JUST LIKE YOU DON'T WANT
TO TELL ME ABOUT YOUR SON,

06:19.052 --> 06:20.754
I WASN'T ABOUT TO TELL YOU
ABOUT MINE!

06:20.754 --> 06:23.223
THAT IS MY BROTHER!
YOU ARE A CRAZY ‐‐

06:23.223 --> 06:25.358
SAY IT, AND I WILL
LAY YOUR ASS OUT

06:25.358 --> 06:26.927
IN THIS HOSPITAL!

06:26.927 --> 06:30.430
YOU LOVE THIS.
YOU...LOVE MAKING ME SUFFER.

06:30.430 --> 06:32.866
OH, GIRL, PLEASE.
THE HELL YOU PUT ME THROUGH?

06:33.934 --> 06:36.069
WHAT THE HELL ARE YOU
LOOKING AT?!

06:36.069 --> 06:37.604
MIND YOUR BUSINESS!

06:37.604 --> 06:38.905
HOW IS BENNY?

06:38.905 --> 06:40.907
YOU NEED TO TELL ME
WHERE YOUR BABY IS.

06:40.907 --> 06:42.375
I DON'T NEED TO TELL YOU
NOTHING!

06:42.375 --> 06:43.677
OKAY, THEN DON'T.

06:47.180 --> 06:49.015
HOW IS MY BROTHER?

06:49.015 --> 06:51.518
I WENT TO THAT LITTLE GIRL'S
FUNERAL,

06:51.518 --> 06:55.922
AND THE ONLY THING ON MY MIND
WAS YOUR BROTHER AND YOUR BABY.

06:55.922 --> 06:58.559
AND YOU WON'T EVEN TELL ME
WHERE HE IS.

06:58.559 --> 07:00.701
DO YOU EVEN KNOW
WHERE HE IS?

07:00.701 --> 07:02.736
I TOLD YOU.

07:02.736 --> 07:06.372
LITTLE GIRL, YOU GOT 24 HOURS
TO BRING ME THAT BABY...

07:08.108 --> 07:09.810
...OR I'M CALLING
THE POLICE.

07:09.810 --> 07:12.012
HMM.

07:12.012 --> 07:13.647
SO DO IT!
AAH!

07:13.647 --> 07:14.815
[ SLAPS ]

07:18.418 --> 07:20.053
I'M‐A CALL 'EM,

07:20.053 --> 07:21.755
AND I'M‐A TELL 'EM THAT YOU
DON'T EVEN KNOW

07:21.755 --> 07:22.956
WHERE YOUR OWN CHILD IS.

07:22.956 --> 07:25.258
YOU DO THIS NOW? NOW?!

07:25.258 --> 07:27.794
YOU WON'T TELL ME
WHERE HE IS!

07:27.794 --> 07:32.533
AND YOU KNOW I LOVE
THAT BABY!

07:32.533 --> 07:34.400
YEAH.

07:34.400 --> 07:36.336
I'M‐A CALL THE POLICE.

07:36.336 --> 07:39.706
I DON'T GIVE A DAMN IF YOU
CALL THE NATIONAL GUARD,

07:39.706 --> 07:42.743
YOU WILL NEVER, EVER
SEE MY CHILD.

07:45.045 --> 07:48.515
AND YOU WILL NEVER...

07:48.515 --> 07:50.450
EVER...

07:50.450 --> 07:52.352
SEE MY CHILD.

07:54.821 --> 07:58.458
ARE YOU GONNA TELL ME
HOW HE IS OR NOT?

07:59.626 --> 08:03.203
AS SOON AS YOU TELL ME
WHERE YOUR BABY IS.

08:06.039 --> 08:07.741
OKAY.

08:09.242 --> 08:11.111
OKAY.

08:13.479 --> 08:16.216
[ PHONE RINGING IN DISTANCE ]

08:19.720 --> 08:21.588
COUNTY HOSPITAL.
EXCUSE ME?

08:21.588 --> 08:23.089
MM‐HMM. YES.

08:24.625 --> 08:26.159
EXCUSE ME.
ARE YOU CRAZY?

08:26.159 --> 08:28.562
YES, BITCH, I AM.

08:28.562 --> 08:31.364
I NEED TO CHECK ON MY BROTHER.
HIS NAME IS BENJAMIN YOUNG.

08:31.364 --> 08:33.734
THE DOCTOR IS NOT HERE.
WELL, WHERE IS HE?

08:33.734 --> 08:35.035
IN SURGERY.

08:35.035 --> 08:37.003
HE WILL MAKE HIS ROUNDS,
AND HE WILL FILL YOU IN.

08:37.003 --> 08:38.204
OH, NO, THAT WON'T DO.

08:38.204 --> 08:40.807
WELL, THAT IS
THE WAY IT GOES.

08:42.509 --> 08:44.578
LET ME TRY THIS AGAIN...
BITCH!

08:44.578 --> 08:46.513
EXCUSE ME?

08:46.513 --> 08:47.981
YOU HEARD ME.

08:47.981 --> 08:49.616
I DON'T KNOW WHO YOU THINK
YOU'RE TALKING TO,

08:49.616 --> 08:52.653
BUT IF YOU WANT TO KEEP THIS
LITTLE $5 AN HOUR JOB,

08:52.653 --> 08:54.588
YOU BETTER GET
YOUR LAZY ASS IN THERE

08:54.588 --> 08:57.658
AND GET SOMEBODY OUT HERE
TO TALK TO ME NOW.

08:57.658 --> 09:01.034
AND DON'T YOU TAKE FOREVER.
GO!

09:01.034 --> 09:02.703
I KNOW YOU CAN WALK
FASTER THAN THAT.

09:02.703 --> 09:04.971
AND DON'T TAKE FOREVER.

09:19.219 --> 09:20.787
[ ENGINE STOPS ]

09:33.333 --> 09:35.035
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

09:50.684 --> 09:51.952
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

10:02.603 --> 10:04.037
[ SNIFFS ]

10:08.742 --> 10:10.076
[ LID CLATTERS ]

10:16.817 --> 10:18.619
THAT WAS EVENTFUL.

10:18.619 --> 10:20.320
YES, IT WAS.

10:21.454 --> 10:25.826
KATHERYN, ARE YOU OKAY?

10:25.826 --> 10:27.093
YES.

10:29.830 --> 10:34.568
YOU WERE ALL SO QUIET
ALL THE WAY OVER HERE.

10:34.568 --> 10:37.037
WOULD ANYONE CARE
TO FILL ME IN?

10:42.843 --> 10:44.778
JIM?

10:49.282 --> 10:50.817
DAVID?

10:55.321 --> 10:56.422
KATHERYN?

11:00.360 --> 11:02.669
OKAY, WELL, LET ME.

11:02.669 --> 11:04.470
WYATT LEFT MY FACILITY,
AND HE ‐‐

11:04.470 --> 11:06.239
HOLD IT.

11:06.239 --> 11:07.240
WHAT?

11:07.240 --> 11:09.910
WAIT.

11:09.910 --> 11:11.344
CELINE?

11:14.548 --> 11:15.982
YES, SIR?

11:15.982 --> 11:17.984
THAT'LL BE ALL FOR TODAY.
YOU CAN GO HOME.

11:17.984 --> 11:18.985
EXCUSE ME?

11:18.985 --> 11:20.654
I SAID THAT'LL BE ALL
FOR TODAY.

11:20.654 --> 11:21.822
YOU CAN GO HOME.

11:21.822 --> 11:23.557
I STILL HAVE A LOT
OF WORK TO DO ‐‐

11:23.557 --> 11:26.727
IT'S FINE. LEAVE IT.
REALLY, GO HOME.

11:28.829 --> 11:29.863
OKAY.

11:29.863 --> 11:31.998
THANK YOU.

11:33.600 --> 11:36.603
MR. CRYER, UH...
[ Sighs ]

11:36.603 --> 11:39.172
I STILL HAVEN'T GOTTEN
THAT CHECK.

11:43.409 --> 11:45.278
OH, OH.

11:45.278 --> 11:47.213
YEAH, I'LL GET IT TO YOU
FIRST THING IN THE MORNING.

11:50.150 --> 11:53.554
YOU KNOW, IT HAS BEEN TWO DAYS
SINCE I ASKED FOR IT, RIGHT?

11:53.554 --> 11:55.388
I KNOW.

11:55.388 --> 11:58.024
BUT I'LL GET IT TO YOU
FIRST THING IN THE MORNING.

11:58.024 --> 12:00.561
OKAY.

12:00.561 --> 12:02.402
BUT I WILL NEED IT
IN THE MORNING.

12:02.402 --> 12:05.706
CELINE, LEAVE. NOW.

12:05.706 --> 12:07.207
[ SIGHS ]
THANK YOU.

12:07.207 --> 12:09.175
YES, SIR.

12:09.175 --> 12:11.545
I'M SORRY.
Y'ALL HAVE A GOOD DAY.

12:11.545 --> 12:14.080
CELINE.

12:14.080 --> 12:15.782
USE THE FRONT DOOR,
PLEASE.

12:15.782 --> 12:17.784
WELL, I WAS JUST GONNA GET
MY PURSE, SIR.

12:17.784 --> 12:19.520
YOUR PURSE IS ON THE FRONT
SEAT OF YOUR CAR.

12:20.754 --> 12:22.956
YES, IT IS.

12:22.956 --> 12:25.091
YOU DO KNOW ME WELL.

12:25.091 --> 12:26.527
YES, I DO.

12:27.493 --> 12:30.363
[ Inhales sharply ]
WELL, THEN...

12:30.363 --> 12:31.665
GOOD‐BYE.

12:31.665 --> 12:33.900
THANK YOU.

12:37.571 --> 12:38.972
[ DOOR OPENS ]

12:41.708 --> 12:45.846
KATHERYN, YOUR STAFF
IS WAY TOO FAMILIAR.

12:45.846 --> 12:47.514
YOU NEED TO FIRE HER.

12:47.514 --> 12:49.583
VERONICA.
WELL, SHE SHOULD.

12:49.583 --> 12:51.785
WELL, BOTH OF YOU SHOULD.

12:51.785 --> 12:53.554
HONEY.
WHAT?

12:54.821 --> 12:57.257
ANYWAY, WHERE WAS I?

12:57.257 --> 12:59.526
WYATT TOOK JEFFERY'S CAR,

12:59.526 --> 13:01.535
WENT TO THE CRACK HOUSE,
GOT HIGH,

13:01.535 --> 13:05.939
AND GOT BEHIND THE WHEEL
IN JEFFERY'S CAR.

13:05.939 --> 13:08.775
AND HIT THAT LITTLE GIRL.

13:08.775 --> 13:11.778
AND HIT HANNA'S SON.

13:13.580 --> 13:15.616
IS THAT ABOUT RIGHT?

13:17.183 --> 13:19.352
YES, IT IS.

13:19.352 --> 13:21.287
DOES HANNA KNOW?

13:21.287 --> 13:22.989
NO.
YES.

13:22.989 --> 13:25.358
JIM, YOU DON'T KNOW THAT.
KATHERYN, WYATT CAME HOME.

13:25.358 --> 13:27.661
HE SAID HE HAD HIT SOMEONE.
SHE HEARD HIM.

13:27.661 --> 13:29.362
SHE'S NOT STUPID.

13:29.362 --> 13:32.265
HER SON.

13:32.265 --> 13:34.200
SHE LOVES HER SON
SO MUCH.

13:34.200 --> 13:35.969
GET A HOLD OF YOURSELF,
KATHERYN.

13:35.969 --> 13:38.639
WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL ME?

13:38.639 --> 13:41.374
I ASKED DAVID TO TELL YOU.

13:41.374 --> 13:43.677
MM.

13:43.677 --> 13:45.512
WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL ME?

13:45.512 --> 13:47.714
WE WERE HANDLING IT.

13:47.714 --> 13:50.183
[ LAUGHS ]

13:50.183 --> 13:51.985
SURELY YOU CAN SEE
HOW IMPORTANT THIS IS.

13:51.985 --> 13:54.387
WE NEED TO FIND THE CAR,
VERONICA.

13:54.387 --> 13:56.557
YES, WE DO.
WHAT?

13:56.557 --> 13:59.593
WE DON'T KNOW WHERE WYATT
LEFT THE CAR.

13:59.593 --> 14:02.636
NOW IT HAS A TRACKING DEVICE
IN IT IN CASE IT'S STOLEN,

14:02.636 --> 14:05.071
BUT THE CAR IS IN YOUR NAME,

14:05.071 --> 14:07.774
AND I DON'T HAVE ACCESS
TO THE PASS CODES.

14:07.774 --> 14:09.910
IS THIS WHAT YOU WERE
LOOKING FOR THE OTHER DAY?

14:09.910 --> 14:11.177
YES.

14:11.177 --> 14:13.013
WHY DIDN'T YOU JUST
SAY SOMETHING?

14:13.013 --> 14:15.348
I WAS HOPING I COULD KEEP YOU
OUT OF THIS MESS.

14:15.348 --> 14:18.051
I AM ALREADY IN THIS MESS,
DAVID!

14:19.419 --> 14:21.588
I NEED YOU TO CALL IT IN.

14:23.489 --> 14:25.792
[ Sighs ] YOU NEED
A POLICE REPORT FOR THAT.

14:25.792 --> 14:26.960
WHAT?

14:26.960 --> 14:28.261
YES, THAT IS THE WAY IT WORKS.

14:28.261 --> 14:30.030
YOU NEED A POLICE REPORT
FOR THAT.

14:30.030 --> 14:31.898
DON'T TELL ME HOW THIS WORKS.
WE'RE JUDGES.

14:31.898 --> 14:33.700
YOU'RE A LAWYER.
MAKE SOMETHING HAPPEN.

14:33.700 --> 14:35.669
I'LL SEE WHAT I CAN DO.

14:38.739 --> 14:42.576
YOU UNDERSTAND THIS IS MY SON'S
LIFE WE'RE TALKING ABOUT HERE.

14:42.576 --> 14:44.310
OH, I UNDERSTAND.

14:44.310 --> 14:46.647
NOT TO MENTION, OURS.

14:46.647 --> 14:47.948
WHAT ABOUT JEFFERY?

14:47.948 --> 14:51.351
IT'S HIS CAR, AND HE HASN'T
REPORTED IT STOLEN.

14:51.351 --> 14:52.653
NOW HE HASN'T DONE ANYTHING,

14:52.653 --> 14:54.988
BUT THE D. A. COULD TIE HIM IN
AS AN ACCESSORY.

14:54.988 --> 14:56.489
YOU KNOW HOW THIS WORKS,
VERONICA.

14:56.489 --> 14:58.391
I KNOW, DAVID!

15:00.767 --> 15:02.669
VERONICA, PLEASE.

15:02.669 --> 15:04.738
WAIT A MINUTE.

15:04.738 --> 15:07.273
YOU ALL ACT AS THOUGH
I DON'T WANT TO HELP, AND I DO.

15:07.273 --> 15:08.441
THEN CALL.

15:08.441 --> 15:10.577
OKAY. WHERE CAN I GO
TO MAKE THE CALL?

15:10.577 --> 15:12.445
JIM'S STUDY.
FINE.

15:12.445 --> 15:13.947
LET ME FIND THE NUMBER.

15:13.947 --> 15:16.116
DAVID, I HAVE AN IDEA.

15:16.116 --> 15:17.651
WHAT IS IT?

15:17.651 --> 15:19.920
YOU AND I NEED TO GO
FOR A DRIVE.

15:21.054 --> 15:22.523
OKAY.

15:22.523 --> 15:24.290
VERONICA, I'LL BE BACK
IN A LITTLE WHILE.

15:24.290 --> 15:25.659
OKAY.

15:25.659 --> 15:27.528
KATHERYN, WHERE ARE THE KEYS
TO WYATT'S CAR?

15:27.528 --> 15:29.329
IN THE SAFE.

15:29.329 --> 15:31.765
GET THEM FOR ME,
WOULD YOU, PLEASE?

15:31.765 --> 15:33.199
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

15:33.199 --> 15:35.168
I'M HANDLING IT.

15:35.168 --> 15:36.837
KEYS, PLEASE.

15:42.108 --> 15:45.646
YES, HARRINGTON.

15:45.646 --> 15:49.415
UH‐HUH. YES?

15:49.415 --> 15:52.418
YES, THAT'S THE VIN NUMBER.

15:52.418 --> 15:57.090
MM‐HMM. OKAY.
AND WHERE IS IT?

15:57.090 --> 15:58.792
OH, NO. NO.
IT HASN'T BEEN STOLEN.

15:58.792 --> 16:01.835
IT'S MY SON.
HE MUST'VE TAKEN IT.

16:01.835 --> 16:04.971
YES.

16:04.971 --> 16:06.840
AND WHAT IS THE ADDRESS,
PLEASE?

16:06.840 --> 16:09.710
ONE MOMENT.

16:09.710 --> 16:13.246
OKAY.

16:13.246 --> 16:16.249
YES.

16:16.249 --> 16:20.554
AND THIS IS WHERE THE CAR IS?
YOU'RE SURE?

16:20.554 --> 16:21.822
OKAY.

16:21.822 --> 16:23.624
AND ONE MORE THING ‐‐

16:23.624 --> 16:25.559
HOW DO I CANCEL THIS
SUBSCRIPTION

16:25.559 --> 16:28.394
AND DISABLE THIS DEVICE?

16:28.394 --> 16:31.698
OH. YOU CAN DO THAT ONLINE?

16:31.698 --> 16:36.537
YES. I WOULD LIKE TO DO THAT.

16:36.537 --> 16:38.238
OKAY.

16:38.238 --> 16:43.309
THANK YOU. UH ‐‐ YES.
I HAVE THE ADDRESS. THANK YOU.

16:43.309 --> 16:44.878
[ BEEP ]

16:46.346 --> 16:47.948
[ CLATTERING ]

16:47.948 --> 16:49.916
[ PAPER RIPS ]

16:49.916 --> 16:51.317
[ EXHALES ]

17:47.781 --> 17:49.983
DID YOU FIND IT?

17:49.983 --> 17:52.318
JEFFERY...

17:54.054 --> 17:55.589
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

17:57.724 --> 17:59.893
MOM.

18:04.671 --> 18:05.772
HELLO.

18:05.772 --> 18:09.009
HI, MS. CRYER.

18:09.009 --> 18:12.345
HI, JEFFERY.

18:12.345 --> 18:13.379
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

18:13.379 --> 18:16.249
I WAS JUST...
TALKING TO WYATT.

18:16.249 --> 18:18.451
ABOUT WHAT?

18:18.451 --> 18:23.389
JUST...CATCHING UP.

18:23.389 --> 18:26.527
WYATT CAN'T HAVE
ANY VISITORS.

18:28.461 --> 18:31.231
YES, MA'AM.

18:31.231 --> 18:32.799
AND, JEFFERY...

18:32.799 --> 18:34.768
WHERE'S YOUR CAR?

18:39.005 --> 18:42.242
UM...

18:42.242 --> 18:44.945
IT WAS ‐‐ IT WAS STOLEN.

18:46.412 --> 18:47.548
STOLEN?

18:50.350 --> 18:52.586
[ Softly ] YEAH.

18:52.586 --> 18:55.756
[ SIGHS ]

18:55.756 --> 18:58.091
CUT THE CRAP, JEFFERY.
WE ALL KNOW.

18:58.091 --> 19:03.136
I ‐‐ I HONESTLY DON'T KNOW
WHERE IT IS, MS. CRYER.

19:04.337 --> 19:06.673
BUT YOU WERE GONNA LIE
TO PROTECT HIM?

19:06.673 --> 19:10.376
IT WAS GONNA ‐‐ I WAS ‐‐
SHE WAS ‐‐

19:10.376 --> 19:12.513
LIE!

19:12.513 --> 19:14.447
DO YOU KNOW WHAT ACCESSORY IS,
JEFFERY?

19:14.447 --> 19:15.782
MOM, I ‐‐

19:15.782 --> 19:18.785
ACCESSORY TO A CRIME.
YOU COULD BE CONVICTED OF IT.

19:18.785 --> 19:21.021
AIDING AND ABETTING.
I DIDN'T ‐‐

19:21.021 --> 19:22.889
VERONICA, HE DID IT
FOR WYATT.

19:22.889 --> 19:23.990
I UNDERSTAND THAT.

19:23.990 --> 19:25.692
AND YOU WOULD DO
ANYTHING FOR HIM?

19:25.692 --> 19:27.761
VERONICA!
[ EXHALES ]

19:27.761 --> 19:29.596
WHAT IS...THIS?

19:34.167 --> 19:37.504
NOTHING.

19:37.504 --> 19:39.372
MY SON.

19:41.307 --> 19:44.845
WHERE IS THE CAR, BOY?

19:46.547 --> 19:50.016
MOM, I REALLY DON'T KNOW
WHERE IT IS.

19:51.685 --> 19:54.454
OKAY.

19:56.056 --> 20:00.133
OKAY.

20:08.575 --> 20:09.710
I HAVE ‐‐ I HAVE TO GO.

20:09.710 --> 20:10.711
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

20:10.711 --> 20:12.145
I'M STAYING WITH A FRIEND.

20:12.145 --> 20:13.279
A FRIEND?
YEAH.

20:13.279 --> 20:15.248
WHICH FRIEND?
YOU DON'T KNOW HER.

20:15.248 --> 20:17.450
HER?

20:17.450 --> 20:19.485
OKAY, GOOD.

20:21.988 --> 20:24.057
BYE, MOM.

20:24.057 --> 20:26.793
JEFFERY...

20:26.793 --> 20:28.061
YES?

20:28.061 --> 20:29.462
YOU LOOK A MESS.

20:29.462 --> 20:30.897
WELL, THIS IS ALL I GOT.

20:30.897 --> 20:33.800
HMM. IT'S YOUR CHOICE, SON.

20:33.800 --> 20:35.235
NO, IT'S YOUR CHOICE.

20:35.235 --> 20:38.071
YOU'RE MEETING ME FOR LUNCH
ON THURSDAY.

20:38.071 --> 20:41.708
JUBILEE. SAME TABLE. NOON.

20:41.708 --> 20:43.544
OKAY.

20:43.544 --> 20:44.545
"OKAY"?

20:44.545 --> 20:46.279
THAT'S WHAT I SAID.

20:48.114 --> 20:51.217
SEE YOU LATER, MS. CRYER.

20:51.217 --> 20:54.721
GOOD‐BYE, JEFFERY.

20:54.721 --> 20:58.625
WHAT'S GOING ON WITH JEFFERY?
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

20:58.625 --> 21:04.004
HMM. I'M TEACHING HIM THE JOYS
OF MANHOOD.

21:04.004 --> 21:06.507
HMM.

21:06.507 --> 21:09.009
WELL...

21:09.009 --> 21:13.146
SO I GUESS THE COMPANY
COULDN'T LOCATE THE CAR?

21:13.146 --> 21:15.849
NO.

21:15.849 --> 21:17.317
SORRY.

21:17.317 --> 21:19.786
THIS IS A MESS.

21:19.786 --> 21:20.921
YES, IT IS.

21:20.921 --> 21:23.657
KATHERYN, DARLING,
I HAVE TO GO.

21:23.657 --> 21:26.727
BUT I WILL CALL YOU LATER.
OKAY.

21:26.727 --> 21:29.896
MY CAR SERVICE
SHOULD BE HERE BY NOW.

21:29.896 --> 21:34.234
IT'S BEEN A LONG DAY.
GET SOME REST.

21:34.234 --> 21:36.102
YES, IT HAS.

21:44.077 --> 21:45.712
[ HELICOPTER WHIRRING,
SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE ]

21:45.712 --> 21:48.081
I KNOW SHE HEARD ME.

21:48.081 --> 21:49.616
OH, LEAVE THAT WOMAN ALONE.

21:49.616 --> 21:52.318
YOU OBVIOUSLY THINK
I'M KIDDING WITH YOU.

21:52.318 --> 21:53.954
THE DOCTOR IS IN SURGERY.

21:53.954 --> 21:56.557
YOU ALREADY SAID THAT.
GO AND FIND HIM.

21:56.557 --> 21:58.559
LADY ‐‐
I AM NOT PLAYING WITH YOU.

21:58.559 --> 22:00.994
SECURITY!

22:00.994 --> 22:04.104
AND WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO,
YOU DAMN RENT‐A‐COP?

22:04.104 --> 22:05.405
GO BACK THERE AND EAT A DONUT.

22:05.405 --> 22:07.808
LADY, LOOK, I AM SORRY
ABOUT YOUR BROTHER ‐‐

22:07.808 --> 22:10.476
GO AND FIND THE DOCTOR!
NOW.

22:10.476 --> 22:12.312
HE IS IN SURGERY.

22:12.312 --> 22:13.647
WHAT'S HIS NAME?

22:13.647 --> 22:15.816
HANDEL. DR. HANDEL.

22:15.816 --> 22:16.850
AND WHERE IS SURGERY?

22:16.850 --> 22:18.919
YOU CANNOT GO IN THERE.
OKAY.

22:18.919 --> 22:20.020
<i>Woman over P. A.:</i>
<i>DR. FORREST,</i>

22:20.020 --> 22:21.588
<i>DIAL 118, PLEASE.</i>

22:21.588 --> 22:23.456
<i>DR. FORREST...</i>

22:23.456 --> 22:26.960
SHE IS CRAZY.

22:30.764 --> 22:32.298
[ TONE BEEPS ]

22:32.298 --> 22:34.267
<i>Man over P. A.:</i>
<i>BLUE TEAM TO I. C. U., PLEASE.</i>

22:34.267 --> 22:35.502
<i>BLUE TEAM, I. C. U.</i>

22:36.537 --> 22:37.871
YOU CAN'T BE IN HERE!

22:37.871 --> 22:39.039
WHICH ONE OF YOU
IS DR. HANDEL?

22:39.039 --> 22:40.273
I AM,
BUT YOU CAN'T BE IN HERE!

22:40.273 --> 22:41.842
I DON'T GIVE A DAMN
WHO IS ON THAT TABLE.

22:41.842 --> 22:42.843
MY BROTHER IS IN HERE

22:42.843 --> 22:44.144
AND YOU NEED TO TELL ME
SOMETHING NOW.

22:44.144 --> 22:45.512
OUT! NOW!
NO!

22:45.512 --> 22:46.513
WHAT IS THE NAME
OF YOUR BROTHER?

22:46.513 --> 22:47.614
BENJAMIN YOUNG.

22:47.614 --> 22:48.982
I'LL COME OUT
TO TALK TO YOU IN A SECOND.

22:48.982 --> 22:50.784
I'M GIVING YOU THREE MINUTES!

22:50.784 --> 22:53.353
GET OUT OF HERE!
YOU COULD KILL THIS PATIENT.

22:53.353 --> 22:55.121
DO I LOOK LIKE
I GIVE A DAMN?!

22:55.121 --> 22:56.222
OUT!

22:56.222 --> 22:58.224
YOUR THREE MINUTES
STARTS NOW.

22:58.224 --> 23:01.134
[ MONITOR BEEPING CONTINUOUSLY ]

23:05.205 --> 23:09.776
YOU GET THAT DONUT?

23:09.776 --> 23:12.278
[ TELEPHONE RINGS IN DISTANCE ]

23:17.684 --> 23:21.688
I WANT BENNY MOVED
TO A PRIVATE HOSPITAL.

23:23.757 --> 23:25.291
DID YOU HEAR ME?

23:25.291 --> 23:28.829
I WANT HIM MOVED
TO A PRIVATE HOSPITAL.

23:28.829 --> 23:30.496
DON'T YOU THINK I WANT
THE SAME THING?

23:30.496 --> 23:31.898
THEN DO IT.

23:31.898 --> 23:36.703
UNLIKE YOU,
I DON'T CON OR SCHEME.

23:36.703 --> 23:40.440
ANYWAY, I CAN'T.

23:40.440 --> 23:44.110
DOESN'T HAVE ANY
HEALTH INSURANCE.

23:47.080 --> 23:48.114
I'M GONNA HAVE HIM MOVED.

23:48.114 --> 23:49.415
NO, YOU'RE NOT.

23:49.415 --> 23:51.552
NOT ON NO CON,
YOU'RE NOT, GIRL.

23:51.552 --> 23:53.587
I'M HAVING HIM MOVED.

23:53.587 --> 23:55.221
YOU TRY IT,

23:55.221 --> 23:57.190
AND THEY'LL BE ROLLING YOUR ASS
TO THE MORGUE

23:57.190 --> 23:58.825
AS HE'S WALKING OUT OF HERE.

23:58.825 --> 24:02.035
YOU ARE SUCH A BITCH!
SAME TO YOU, DAUGHTER.

24:02.035 --> 24:04.505
YOU NEED TO
CALM THE HELL DOWN,

24:04.505 --> 24:06.339
BEFORE THEY START
TREATING HIM WORSE.

24:06.339 --> 24:07.841
YOU KEEP TALKING TO THESE
PEOPLE LIKE THAT,

24:07.841 --> 24:09.576
THEY'LL NEVER LET US SEE HIM.

24:09.576 --> 24:12.646
SIT THERE AND THUMP YOUR BIBLE
LIKE USUAL.

24:12.646 --> 24:15.448
RIGHT UPSIDE YOUR HEAD
IN ABOUT TWO SECONDS.

24:15.448 --> 24:17.584
THAT'S SO CHRISTIAN.

24:19.886 --> 24:21.655
BENJAMIN YOUNG?

24:21.655 --> 24:24.290
ARE YOU DR. HANDEL?

24:24.290 --> 24:25.325
YES, YOUNG LADY.

24:25.325 --> 24:26.927
WE JUST MET BACK IN SURGERY,
REMEMBER?

24:26.927 --> 24:30.130
YEAH. UM, HOW IS HE?
WHAT'S GOING ON?

24:30.130 --> 24:31.832
NOT GOOD.

24:31.832 --> 24:34.167
I‐I NEED TO SEE HIM,
AND I NEED TO SEE HIM NOW.

24:34.167 --> 24:37.270
NURSE, CAN YOU TAKE MISS...
YOUNG.

24:37.270 --> 24:39.840
...YOUNG TO SEE
BENJAMIN YOUNG, PLEASE?

24:39.840 --> 24:40.907
THANK YOU.

24:40.907 --> 24:42.776
CAN I GO BACK
TO SURGERY NOW?

24:42.776 --> 24:44.277
DO I LOOK LIKE YOUR BOSS?

24:44.277 --> 24:45.979
WELL, YOU SURE ACT LIKE IT.

24:45.979 --> 24:48.882
WELL, THEN GET BACK TO WORK.

24:48.882 --> 24:50.717
THIS WAY.

24:55.589 --> 24:59.459
[ MONITOR BEEPING CONTINUOUSLY ]

25:01.668 --> 25:03.737
THERE HE IS.

25:17.551 --> 25:21.021
BENNY.

25:21.021 --> 25:23.289
[ Voice breaking ]
DON'T TOUCH HIM.

25:26.627 --> 25:31.064
WHAT IS GOING ON WITH HIM?

25:31.064 --> 25:33.534
TELL ME.

25:33.534 --> 25:35.301
PLEASE.

25:37.638 --> 25:40.306
[ Whispers ] PLEASE.

25:42.709 --> 25:44.945
HE'S ON LIFE SUPPORT.

25:46.913 --> 25:50.817
AND THEY WANT ME
TO TAKE HIM OFF IT.

25:50.817 --> 25:55.021
WHY? SO HE CAN DIE?

25:55.021 --> 25:58.324
THAT'S WHAT THEY WANT.
[ SNIFFLES ]

25:58.324 --> 26:01.501
YOU CAN'T DO THAT.

26:01.501 --> 26:03.504
OH, GIRL, HUSH.
[ Sniffles ]

26:07.307 --> 26:08.809
I WOULD NEVER DO THAT.

26:12.579 --> 26:16.482
THESE FOLKS ARE NOT GONNA
LET HIM STAY IN THIS BED.

26:16.482 --> 26:18.819
THEY NEED IT.

26:21.254 --> 26:24.190
I CAN'T DO THIS.

26:26.560 --> 26:28.529
[ Whispers ] I CAN'T.

26:33.466 --> 26:37.137
[ CRYING, SNIFFLES ]

26:37.137 --> 26:40.106
HEY, BABY.

26:40.106 --> 26:41.742
IT'S MAMA. [ Sniffles ]

26:45.946 --> 26:49.115
I KNOW YOU HEAR ME.

26:49.115 --> 26:52.418
[ CRYING ]

26:52.418 --> 26:57.958
I NEED YOU TO COME BACK
TO ME, BABY, OKAY?

26:57.958 --> 27:00.761
[ CONTINUES CRYING ]

27:00.761 --> 27:05.839
YOU NEED TO COME BACK TO ME
NOW, BABY, OKAY, BABY?

27:05.839 --> 27:08.041
[ SNIFFLES ]

27:08.041 --> 27:09.943
I KNOW YOU CAN DO THIS.

27:11.177 --> 27:15.281
YOU KNOW WHAT I'M GONNA SAY.

27:15.281 --> 27:20.687
OH, IN THE NAME OF JESUS.
COME ON NOW.

27:20.687 --> 27:24.758
I NEED YOU TO COME
BACK TO ME, OKAY?

27:24.758 --> 27:27.093
COME ON BACK, BABY.

27:27.093 --> 27:30.797
YOU FIGHT.

27:30.797 --> 27:35.669
[ CRYING ]

27:35.669 --> 27:37.738
[ SHUDDERS ]

27:37.738 --> 27:40.774
[ SOBBING ]

27:50.684 --> 27:53.887
[ OPERA MUSIC PLAYING ]

27:53.887 --> 27:58.659
♪♪♪♪♪♪

28:22.188 --> 28:24.157
[ BEEP, MUSIC STOPS ]

28:24.157 --> 28:25.659
OH, DON'T LET ME
STOP YOU.

28:25.659 --> 28:26.927
RUDE.

28:26.927 --> 28:29.362
RUDE? I DIDN'T ‐‐
I DIDN'T WANNA INTERRUPT YOU.

28:29.362 --> 28:31.164
WELL, YOU DID.

28:31.164 --> 28:34.234
SORRY.

28:34.234 --> 28:35.435
UM...

28:35.435 --> 28:37.270
HOW LONG ARE YOU GONNA BE
STAYING HERE?

28:37.270 --> 28:39.806
AH, WELL, UM,

28:39.806 --> 28:42.576
I WAS WONDERING WHEN YOU WERE
GONNA ASK ME THAT.

28:42.576 --> 28:47.180
MY MOM AND I,
SHE ‐‐ SHE CUT ME OFF.

28:47.180 --> 28:49.516
[ Scoffs ]
WELCOME TO THE CLUB.

28:49.516 --> 28:51.017
YEAH?

28:51.017 --> 28:53.019
WELL,
TO HELL WITH THEM, RIGHT?

28:53.019 --> 28:55.922
WHAT IS THIS NEW ATTITUDE
OF YOURS?

28:55.922 --> 28:57.524
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

28:57.524 --> 28:59.626
YOU'RE DIFFERENT.

28:59.626 --> 29:00.767
YEAH.

29:00.767 --> 29:04.137
AND IT FEELS <i>GOOD.</i>

29:04.137 --> 29:05.506
YEAH?

29:05.506 --> 29:07.774
YEAH.

29:07.774 --> 29:09.543
REALLY GOOD.

29:09.543 --> 29:11.477
I CAN TELL.

29:11.477 --> 29:13.980
YEP.

29:13.980 --> 29:16.817
YOU TAKING YOUR MEDS?

29:16.817 --> 29:18.985
YES, DAD.

29:18.985 --> 29:20.987
I WAS JUST ASKING.

29:20.987 --> 29:23.189
I'M GOOD.

29:23.189 --> 29:25.358
OKAY.

29:27.327 --> 29:30.463
SO, WHY DID YOU AND YOUR MOM
GET INTO IT?

29:31.998 --> 29:34.134
[ Sighs ] IT'S A LONG STORY.

29:34.134 --> 29:36.837
ARE YOU GAY?

29:36.837 --> 29:38.171
YES.

29:38.171 --> 29:40.006
HMM.
[ SCOFFS ]

29:40.006 --> 29:42.042
SO CANDACE WAS RIGHT.

29:42.042 --> 29:44.344
YEAH, SHE WAS RIGHT.

29:44.344 --> 29:47.681
WELL, OKAY.

29:47.681 --> 29:49.182
THAT'S IT?

29:49.182 --> 29:51.351
YEAH, I DON'T CARE.

29:51.351 --> 29:54.420
IT'S SO FUNNY HOW PEOPLE
WORRY ABOUT COMING OUT,

29:54.420 --> 29:56.523
AND THEN WHEN THEY DO,
NO ONE REALLY CARES.

29:56.523 --> 29:59.526
ALL I CARE ABOUT IS MAKING
THIS A GIRLS DEN AGAIN.

29:59.526 --> 30:01.768
SO, WHEN ARE YOU MOVING OUT?

30:01.768 --> 30:05.438
I WILL BE MOVING OUT SOON.

30:05.438 --> 30:06.940
GOOD.

30:06.940 --> 30:10.143
OKAY.

30:10.143 --> 30:13.313
I'M SORRY, I DON'T MEAN
TO MAKE YOU FEEL UNCOMFORTABLE.

30:13.313 --> 30:16.049
NO, NO, NO, IT'S FINE,
THIS IS A TIGHT SPACE.

30:16.049 --> 30:17.183
I‐I GET IT.

30:17.183 --> 30:18.451
YEAH, IT IS.

30:18.451 --> 30:20.186
I'LL BE OUT
AS SOON AS I CAN.

30:20.186 --> 30:22.188
GOOD.

30:22.188 --> 30:25.659
[ SIGHS ]

30:25.659 --> 30:26.960
JEFFERY?

30:26.960 --> 30:28.461
YEAH?

30:32.298 --> 30:35.468
DO YOU KNOW WHERE I COULD, UH,
BUY A GUN?

30:37.003 --> 30:39.372
WHY DO YOU NEED A GUN?

30:43.176 --> 30:45.712
I JUST...WANT ONE.

30:45.712 --> 30:49.382
BUT WHY?

30:55.989 --> 30:59.159
[ Singsongy ] NEVER MIND.

30:59.159 --> 31:03.369
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

31:08.509 --> 31:11.144
YES, HER NAME IS HANNA YOUNG.

31:13.046 --> 31:15.882
I WANT YOU TO FOLLOW HER.
I WANT YOU TO...

31:15.882 --> 31:18.585
FIND OUT EVERYTHING
YOU CAN ABOUT HER.

31:18.585 --> 31:23.156
SHE'D BE AT COUNTY HOSPITAL
VISITING HER SON BENNY YOUNG.

31:23.156 --> 31:24.891
YES.

31:24.891 --> 31:27.227
NO.

31:27.227 --> 31:28.428
I JUST WANT INFORMATION.

31:28.428 --> 31:29.596
I WANNA KNOW WHAT SHE KNOWS

31:29.596 --> 31:31.264
AND I WANNA KNOW
HOW SHE KNOWS IT, OKAY?

31:31.264 --> 31:34.868
ARE WE CLEAR?

31:34.868 --> 31:36.970
THANK YOU.

31:36.970 --> 31:38.672
[ BEEP ]

31:38.672 --> 31:39.706
[ PHONE THUDS ]

31:41.508 --> 31:44.377
KATHERYN!

31:44.377 --> 31:47.213
YOU TALK TO VERONICA?

31:47.213 --> 31:48.314
SHE FIND THE CAR,
BY ANY CHANCE?

31:48.314 --> 31:50.483
NO.

31:50.483 --> 31:53.520
NO.

31:53.520 --> 31:56.657
DAMN IT.

31:56.657 --> 31:58.458
IT'S ALL RIGHT,
I HAVE ANOTHER PLAN IN PLACE.

31:58.458 --> 32:01.367
I HAVE TO GO SEE HER.

32:01.367 --> 32:02.736
SEE WHO?

32:02.736 --> 32:03.737
HANNA.

32:03.737 --> 32:05.872
NO, THAT'S A BAD IDEA.
BAD IDEA.

32:05.872 --> 32:07.240
WHY?

32:07.240 --> 32:09.576
KATHERYN, WE HAVE TO ACT
LIKE EVERYTHING IS NORMAL, OKAY?

32:09.576 --> 32:10.977
EVERYTHING IS FINE.

32:10.977 --> 32:14.280
LET'S JUST WAIT TILL SHE COMES
BACK TO WORK ON HER OWN.

32:14.280 --> 32:15.982
JIM, IT IS HER SON.

32:15.982 --> 32:19.485
AND IT'S ALSO OURS.
I UNDERSTAND.

32:34.300 --> 32:38.004
KATHERYN,
YOU'VE HAD A VERY LONG DAY.

32:38.004 --> 32:41.642
YOU SHOULD GET SOME REST.

32:41.642 --> 32:44.845
"GO REST"? [ Scoffs ]

32:44.845 --> 32:47.247
REST?

32:47.247 --> 32:50.216
HOW CAN I REST, JIM?
[ Sobbing ]

32:53.453 --> 32:55.021
BABY, YOU'RE FALLING APART.

32:55.021 --> 32:57.123
REALLY?

32:57.123 --> 32:59.492
YES.

32:59.492 --> 33:02.769
YOU NEED TO HOLD IT TOGETHER,
KATHERYN.

33:02.769 --> 33:04.397
NOW MORE THAN EVER.

33:04.397 --> 33:10.381
YES, I ‐‐ I HAVE TO
HOLD EVERYTHING IN, DON'T I?

33:10.611 --> 33:14.414
'CAUSE I'M KATHERYN CRYER.
I DON'T HAVE A SOUL, DO I, JIM?

33:14.414 --> 33:17.317
[ Whispers ] HEY, HEY.
I KNOW.

33:17.317 --> 33:19.485
DON'T TOUCH ME!
HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY. HEY, HEY ‐‐

33:19.485 --> 33:21.321
THIS IS YOUR FAULT, JIM!
[ Sobbing ]

33:21.321 --> 33:25.358
KATHERYN, KATHERYN,
HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY.

33:25.358 --> 33:28.662
GET IT OUT. GET IT OUT.
[ SOBBING ]

33:43.910 --> 33:47.681
JIM!
JIM.

33:47.681 --> 33:48.915
GOOD MORNING.

33:48.915 --> 33:50.450
HOW ARE YOU?

33:50.450 --> 33:51.818
I'M GOOD.

33:51.818 --> 33:54.354
I WAS JUST TELLING DAVID
HOW REALLY GOOD

33:54.354 --> 33:55.922
YOU BOTH WERE YESTERDAY.

33:55.922 --> 33:57.390
GOT A LOT OF PICK‐UP.

33:57.390 --> 34:01.735
AND JUST AS I THOUGHT,
YOUR OPPONENT'S ANNOUNCEMENT ‐‐

34:01.735 --> 34:03.369
THANK YOU.
SURE.

34:03.369 --> 34:04.705
WAS MET WITH A LOT
OF NEGATIVITY

34:04.705 --> 34:06.673
FOR NOT BEING SENSITIVE
TO THIS.

34:06.673 --> 34:08.308
YOU SEE?

34:08.308 --> 34:10.243
YES, YOU WERE RIGHT.

34:12.312 --> 34:13.780
I THINK IT'S TIME FOR
THE TWO OF YOU

34:13.780 --> 34:15.348
TO RETIRE FROM THE BENCH.

34:15.348 --> 34:18.619
SO BARRING ANY MORE SURPRISES,
WE ANNOUNCE NEXT MONDAY.

34:20.153 --> 34:21.421
SURE.

34:21.421 --> 34:26.159
JIM? ARE YOU OKAY WITH THIS?

34:27.894 --> 34:31.164
YES. I'M GOOD WITH IT.
[ Chuckles ]

34:31.164 --> 34:33.667
GOOD.

34:33.667 --> 34:36.737
I'LL NEED BOTH OF YOUR FAMILIES
AT THE PRESS CONFERENCE.

34:36.737 --> 34:38.371
[ DOOR OPENS ]

34:40.306 --> 34:42.108
CANDACE.

34:42.108 --> 34:44.711
JIM, I NEED TO TALK TO YOU.
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

34:46.513 --> 34:50.050
YOU NEED TO LEAVE THIS OFFICE.

34:50.050 --> 34:52.318
DON'T TOUCH ME.

34:52.318 --> 34:53.386
HI.

34:56.456 --> 34:57.591
PLEASE.

34:57.591 --> 35:00.293
LET'S GO INTO MY OFFICE.
WE CAN TALK THERE.

35:00.293 --> 35:01.434
NO.

35:01.434 --> 35:03.036
OKAY.

35:03.036 --> 35:05.939
THIS LOOKS LIKE IT COULD BE
IMPORTANT.

35:05.939 --> 35:08.642
MAGGIE, CAN WE FINISH
OUR BUSINESS IN MY OFFICE?

35:08.642 --> 35:11.712
YEAH, THAT SOUNDS LIKE
A GOOD IDEA.

35:11.712 --> 35:14.981
GOOD IDEA.
JIM.

35:19.853 --> 35:22.055
LEAVE IT OPEN.

35:22.055 --> 35:25.158
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS
IN DISTANCE ]

35:29.930 --> 35:31.665
WHAT THE HELL ARE YOU
DOING IN MY OFFICE?

35:31.665 --> 35:35.501
I NEED YOU TO HELP MY BROTHER.

35:35.501 --> 35:36.903
YOU NEED ME TO WHAT?

35:36.903 --> 35:39.673
HE WAS IN A CAR ACCIDENT.
HE WAS HIT BY A DRUNK DRIVER.

35:42.142 --> 35:44.044
DOES HANNA KNOW ABOUT THIS?

35:44.044 --> 35:47.514
HERE.

35:47.514 --> 35:50.016
WHAT THE HELL ARE THOSE?

35:50.016 --> 35:54.487
THE CAR KEYS...
AND $30,000.

35:54.487 --> 35:56.056
THAT'S ALL I HAVE LEFT.

35:59.893 --> 36:02.769
I'LL GET AN ABORTION.

36:02.769 --> 36:06.206
PLEASE, JIM.

36:06.206 --> 36:09.409
I NEED YOU TO HELP HIM.

36:09.409 --> 36:11.411
JIM...

36:11.411 --> 36:14.214
I NEED YOU TO HELP MY BROTHER.

36:14.214 --> 36:16.482
HE NEEDS TO BE
IN A PRIVATE HOSPITAL

36:16.482 --> 36:20.353
AND I KNOW YOU CAN
MAKE THAT HAPPEN.

36:20.353 --> 36:22.022
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

36:22.022 --> 36:26.359
JIM, PLEASE.

36:26.359 --> 36:28.662
PLEASE?

36:28.662 --> 36:30.363
I'LL DO ANYTHING.

36:34.601 --> 36:36.036
I'LL LEAVE AMANDA ALONE.

36:42.275 --> 36:44.077
I'M SORRY, CANDACE.

36:47.313 --> 36:50.350
JIM... [ Sniffles ]

36:50.350 --> 36:52.886
PLEASE.

36:55.789 --> 36:57.891
CAN'T HELP YOU.

36:59.926 --> 37:02.235
YOU WON'T HELP ME.

37:03.937 --> 37:07.406
LET ME SEE IF I GOT THIS
STRAIGHT, OKAY?

37:10.143 --> 37:12.779
A WHILE AGO,
I MADE A PHONE CALL.

37:12.779 --> 37:14.814
I CALLED A HOOKER.

37:14.814 --> 37:18.284
SHE MET ME AT A HOTEL ROOM.
WE HAD A GREAT TIME.

37:18.284 --> 37:25.358
THEN SAID HOOKER
BLACKMAILS ME FOR $100,000.

37:25.358 --> 37:30.931
SAID HOOKER BLACKMAILS ME
FOR A LITTLE RED SPORTS CAR.

37:30.931 --> 37:34.535
I GAVE THAT WHORE
EVERYTHING SHE WANTED.

37:34.535 --> 37:37.804
EVERYTHING.

37:37.804 --> 37:43.610
YOU KNOW WHAT THAT WHORE
HAD THE BALLS TO DO?

37:43.610 --> 37:47.280
WHEN SHE GOT PREGNANT
AND I ASKED HER

37:47.280 --> 37:49.315
TO HAVE AN ABORTION
THAT I WOULD PAY FOR,

37:49.315 --> 37:51.284
SHE SAID NO.

37:55.021 --> 37:57.624
NOW THAT WHORE IS STANDING
IN MY OFFICE

37:57.624 --> 38:00.260
SAYING THAT SHE WILL
LEAVE MY DAUGHTER ALONE,

38:00.260 --> 38:02.002
SHE WILL GIVE ME
THE CAR BACK,

38:02.002 --> 38:06.840
SHE WILL GIVE ME $30,000
OUT OF $100,000 BACK.

38:09.009 --> 38:12.112
NOT GONNA HAPPEN.

38:12.112 --> 38:15.816
WON'T DO IT.

38:15.816 --> 38:17.383
NO.

38:17.383 --> 38:20.253
YOU WON'T HELP ME?

38:20.253 --> 38:24.324
APPARENTLY,
THE WHORE IS HARD OF HEARING.

38:28.829 --> 38:32.298
I KNOW YOU DON'T LIVE YOUR LIFE
WITH REGRETS.

38:34.100 --> 38:35.736
BUT I PROMISE YOU,

38:35.736 --> 38:41.241
YOU WILL REGRET THIS LIKE
NOTHING YOU'VE EVER DONE BEFORE.

38:41.241 --> 38:44.210
CAN'T TELL YOU
HOW SCARED I AM.

38:44.210 --> 38:46.312
OH, YOU SHOULD BE.

38:50.951 --> 38:54.521
[ INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER ]

38:54.521 --> 39:03.804
♪♪ WHY SHOULD I FEEL
DISCOURAGED? ♪♪

39:03.804 --> 39:06.707
♪♪ AND WHY ♪♪

39:06.707 --> 39:14.748
♪♪ SHOULD THE SHADOWS
COME? ♪♪

39:14.748 --> 39:18.384
♪♪ WHY ♪♪

39:18.384 --> 39:25.759
♪♪ SHOULD MY HEART
FEEL LONELY ♪♪

39:25.759 --> 39:31.064
♪♪ AND LONG FOR HEAVEN ♪♪

39:31.064 --> 39:32.398
♪♪ AND HOME ‐‐ ♪♪

39:32.398 --> 39:34.601
I'M SORRY,
VISITING HOURS ARE OVER.

39:34.601 --> 39:37.571
CAN'T I JUST STAY ‐‐

39:37.571 --> 39:40.440
I'M SORRY.
IT'S AGAINST THE RULES.

39:42.609 --> 39:44.978
THANK YOU.

39:44.978 --> 39:48.014
[ MONITOR BEEPING CONTINUOUSLY ]

39:52.252 --> 40:01.702
♪♪ WHEN JESUS IS MY PORTION ♪♪

40:01.702 --> 40:03.236
♪♪ A CONSTANT... ♪♪

40:03.236 --> 40:04.571
[ KISSES ]

40:04.571 --> 40:07.307
♪♪ ...FRIEND IS HE ♪♪

40:07.307 --> 40:09.375
[ KISSES ]

40:09.375 --> 40:14.014
♪♪ THE SPARROW ♪♪

40:14.014 --> 40:16.883
♪♪ AND I KNOW ♪♪

40:16.883 --> 40:21.888
♪♪ HE WATCHES OVER YOU AND ME ♪♪

40:24.157 --> 40:27.227
I LOVE YOU. I'LL BE BACK.

40:34.835 --> 40:37.003
<i>Woman over P. A.:</i>
<i>YOUR ATTENTION, PLEASE...</i>

40:37.003 --> 40:38.038
HANNA YOUNG?

40:38.038 --> 40:39.506
<i>...VISITING HOURS ARE OVER.</i>

40:39.506 --> 40:41.041
YES?

40:41.041 --> 40:44.477
DETECTIVE BYRON MARSHALL.

40:44.477 --> 40:48.749
I'VE BEEN WAITING FOR YOU
TO COME OUT OF THERE.

40:48.749 --> 40:50.116
WHAT CAN I DO FOR YOU?

40:50.116 --> 40:52.185
I'M TRYING TO INVESTIGATE
YOUR SON'S CASE.

40:52.185 --> 40:55.756
MY SON'S CASE?
YES.

40:55.756 --> 40:57.824
WE'RE TRYING TO FIND OUT
WHO DID THIS TO HIM.

40:57.824 --> 41:00.026
ARE YOU?

41:00.026 --> 41:01.835
YES.

41:01.835 --> 41:03.269
WHAT CAN YOU TELL ME?

41:03.269 --> 41:06.807
I CAN TELL YOU A LOT.

41:06.807 --> 41:09.142
OKAY. I'M LISTENING.

41:09.142 --> 41:11.244
WOULD YOU LIKE TO TALK
OVER A CUP OF COFFEE?

41:11.244 --> 41:12.613
NO.

41:12.613 --> 41:17.651
OKAY, YOU WANNA TALK HERE?

41:17.651 --> 41:20.854
I THINK I KNOW WHO DID THIS.

41:20.854 --> 41:22.989
YOU DO?

41:25.826 --> 41:27.528
YES.

41:30.797 --> 41:33.867
<i>NEXT ON "THE HAVES</i>
<i>AND THE HAVE NOTS"...</i>

41:33.867 --> 41:35.501
MAYBE I SHOULD JUST CONFESS.

41:35.501 --> 41:37.738
YOU NEED TO KEEP THIS
WHOLE THING A SECRET, SON.

41:37.738 --> 41:39.706
I'M AFTER JIM.

41:39.706 --> 41:41.041
NO, NO, NO, NO.

41:41.041 --> 41:43.009
I'M GONNA KILL MY PARENTS.

41:43.009 --> 41:44.645
WHAT?
[ POP SOUND ]

41:44.645 --> 41:45.812
THE CLOCK IS TICKIN'.

41:45.812 --> 41:47.147
FOR WHAT?

41:47.147 --> 41:48.515
FOR YOU TO EITHER BRING ME
THAT BABY

41:48.515 --> 41:50.250
OR TELL ME WHERE HE IS.

41:50.250 --> 41:51.685
I'M A MOTHER, JIM.

41:51.685 --> 41:52.686
OH.

41:52.686 --> 41:54.387
WHY WON'T SHE LET ME HELP HER?

41:54.387 --> 41:55.722
SHE DOESN'T TRUST YOU.
THAT'S WHY.

41:55.722 --> 41:58.058
YOU TAKING ME TO COURT?
YES.

41:58.058 --> 41:59.159
YOU KNOW GOOD AND DAMN WELL

41:59.159 --> 42:00.585
I DON'T HAVE THE MONEY
TO FIGHT THIS!
